# Story 3.5: Auto-Refresh Positions

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 3 - Map & Fleet Visualization
- **Status:** done
- **Implemented:** 2025-12-28
- **Session:** SESSION-004

## User Story
As **Diana (Dispatcher)**,
I want **map positions to auto-refresh**,
So that **I see current train locations without manual refresh**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status |
|----|----------|--------|
| AC1 | Positions refresh every 30 seconds | PASS |
| AC2 | Refresh is non-disruptive (no full reload) | PASS |
| AC3 | Last update timestamp shown | PASS |
| AC4 | Manual refresh button available | PASS |

## Implementation Details

### Auto-Refresh Logic
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  const interval = setInterval(() => {
    refetchTrains();
  }, 30000);
  return () => clearInterval(interval);
}, []);
```

### UI Elements
- "Last updated: X seconds ago" indicator
- Refresh button with loading spinner
- Subtle animation on marker position change

## Testability Concern
30-second auto-refresh may cause timing issues in E2E tests.
Recommendation: Mock timer or disable auto-refresh in test environment.

## Dev Notes
30-second interval balances freshness with server load.
Demo can show positions updating in real-time.

